         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Christmas ¶ 1890. ¶  ¶ I am pleased, highly esteemed Doctor, that your long-standing studies of the Characeae can be utilized for Australia, particularly in a connected and illustrated work. ¶  I am p...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">90.12.25</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Otto Nordstedt</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Handskr. avdl., Universitetsbibliotek, Lund.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">Weihnacht</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">1890.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Es freuet mich, hochgeehrter Herr Doctor, dass Ihre vieljährigen Studien der Characeen für Australien besonders in einem zusammen hängenden und illustrirten Werke verwerthet werden können. Ich bin bereit, Ihnen für </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">jede</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Decade £ 10 (Zehn Pfund Sterling) als Subsidie zu Gebot zu stellen, wofür mir ja Exemplare geliefert werden könnten. Mir scheint, es wäre am Besten, jede Tafel un-numerirt zu lassen, so dass zwanglos diejenigen Arten nach und nach zuerst illustrirt werden, von welchen zur Zeit das vollständigste Material vorhanden ist bei Ihnen. Das Erscheinen der ersten Decade würde dann manche Australische wissenschaftlich denkende Ansiedler zum besondern Herbeischaffen von mehr Material der Characeen ermuntern. Am Schluss des Werkes könnte ja ein systematischer Index erscheinen zum Ordnen der losen Platten und auch </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">losen</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Blätter von einzelnen Beschreibungen. So habe ich es auch mit meiner Eucalyptography gethan.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich würde rathen, die neue Nitella vom Georgina-River (tropisches östliches Austr.) </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">nicht Neptuni</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> zu nennen trotz des Tridents, weil Neptun der </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Meeres</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">-Gott der alten Griechen und Roemer war, während diese Nitella in </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">un</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">-salzigem </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">seichtem</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> Wasser </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">weit</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> im </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Inlande vorkommt</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="">. Vielleicht erlauben Sie, diese Pflanze N. Nordstedti genannt zu werden, wenn nicht schon Ihnen eine Art gewidmet ist.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Mit bestem Neujahrs Gruss Ihr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">Bei den Arten sollte die strengste </seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Priorität</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style=""> herrschen, was Al. Br. nicht immer beachtete.</seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <seg style="">
                  <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich habe mir seit langer Zeit unendliche Mühe für die Förderung der antarct. </seg>Expedition Nordenskiölds gegeben.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">Christmas</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">1890.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am pleased, highly esteemed Doctor, that your long-standing studies of the <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name> can be utilized for Australia, particularly in a connected and illustrated work.<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Nordstedt (1891).</p>
               </note> I am prepared to put £10 (Ten pounds sterling) at your disposal for <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">each</hi>
               </seg> decade as subsidy, for which copies could be supplied to me. It seems to me it would be best to leave each plate unnumbered, so that unrestrictedly those species are first illustrated gradually of which the most complete material is available to you at the time. The publication of the first decade would then encourage several scientifically minded Australian settlers to special collection of more material of <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name>. At the conclusion of the work a systematic index could certainly appear for the arrangement of the loose plates and also the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">loose</hi>
               </seg> pages of individual descriptions. I have done such with my Eucalyptography.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">B79.13.11 and following Decades.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I would advise <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">not</hi>
               </seg> to name the new <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Nitella</seg> from Georgina River<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Qld.</p>
               </note> (tropical east Australia) <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Neptuni </seg>in spite of the trident, because Neptune was the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">sea</hi>
               </seg> god of the old Greeks and Romans, whereas this <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Nitella</seg>
               <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">occurs</hi>
               </seg>
               <seg style="font-style: italic; "> </seg>in non-saline <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">shallow</hi>
               </seg> water <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">far</hi>
               </seg> in the <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">inland</hi>
               </seg>. Perhaps you would allow this plant to be named <seg style="font-style: italic; ">N. Nordstedti</seg>
               <seg style="">,</seg>
               <note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">The <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Nitella</seg> from Georgina River was named <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Nitella partita</seg> in Nordstedt (1891), plate 1. There was already a <seg style="font-style: italic; ">N. nordstedtiana</seg> from 1890 (see AlgaeBase, accessed 29 July 2020).</p>
               </note> if a species is not already dedicated to you.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With best New Year greetings your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">With species the strictest <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">priority</hi>
               </seg> should prevail, which Al. Braun did not always follow.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For a long time I have taken infinite trouble for the promotion of Nordenskiöld's antarctic expedition.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Characeae">Characeae</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Nitella%20Neptuni">Nitella Neptuni</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Nitella%20Nordstedti">Nitella Nordstedti</name>
            </p>
         </div>
      </body>
